@startuml seq-purpose-cantonment
title Purpose cantonment v1.3.0 - propagation-only credential refused outside the management route

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Caller code" as App
participant "createHttpSignedFetchClient\n(signer)" as Signer
participant "buildHttpSignedHeaders" as Build
participant "signRequest" as SignReq
collections "Target API" as Target
participant "verifyHttpSignature" as Verify
participant "nonceStore" as Nonce
database "Redis (target)" as Redis

note over Target
  Target initialized with
  internalManagementRoute: "/api/internal/hmac".
  Credential "self_propagation_signer" was
  previously stored with purpose:"propagation-only".
end note

== Case A: signed call on the internal management route -> accepted ==
App -> Signer : signed POST /api/internal/hmac\n(propagate another credential)
Signer -> Build : build headers
Build -> SignReq : signRequest
SignReq --> Build : signature
Build --> Signer : Headers{x-client-id,x-timestamp,x-nonce,x-signature}
Signer -> Target : POST /api/internal/hmac
Target -> Verify : verifyHttpSignature({\n  internalManagementRoute:"/api/internal/hmac",\n  ...})
Verify -> Redis : credentialStore.getClientRecord(\n  "self_propagation_signer")
Redis --> Verify : { secretHash, purpose:"propagation-only", ... }
Verify -> Verify : signature compares (constant-time)
Verify -> Nonce : consume(clientId:nonce:timestamp)
Nonce --> Verify : ok
Verify -> Verify : record.purpose == "propagation-only"\n&& normalizeRoutePath(path) == internalManagementRoute\n-> PASS
Verify --> Target : VerifiedHttpRequest
Target --> App : 201 propagation accepted

== Case B: signed call on a business route -> refused ==
App -> Signer : signed POST /secure/widgets\n(business payload)
Signer -> Build : build headers
Build -> SignReq : signRequest
SignReq --> Build : signature
Signer -> Target : POST /secure/widgets
Target -> Verify : verifyHttpSignature(...)
Verify -> Redis : credentialStore.getClientRecord(\n  "self_propagation_signer")
Redis --> Verify : { secretHash, purpose:"propagation-only", ... }
Verify -> Verify : signature compares OK
Verify -> Nonce : consume(clientId:nonce:timestamp)
Nonce --> Verify : ok (nonce is burnt)
note right of Verify
  Nonce consumed BEFORE the cantonment check
  so a misuse attempt cannot retry inside the
  skew window with a different path.
end note
Verify -> Verify : record.purpose == "propagation-only"\n&& path != internalManagementRoute\n-> FAIL
Verify -> Target : throw PROPAGATION_ONLY_FORBIDDEN (403)
Target --> App : 403 {error:"PROPAGATION_ONLY_FORBIDDEN",\n  message:"... restricted to the internal management route"}

== Case C: message track refuses propagation-only credentials outright ==
note over Target, Redis
  Message store has no path concept.
  hmacMessageAuth.signMessage and
  hmacMessageAuth.verifyMessage refuse
  any record carrying
  purpose:"propagation-only" with
  PROPAGATION_ONLY_FORBIDDEN (403),
  before any signature work.
end note

@enduml
